The '''Penrhyn language''' is a [[Cook Islands Maori]] dialectal variant<ref>"[http://www.paclii.org/ck/legis/num_act/trma2003130/ Te Reo Maori Act]" (2003)</ref> belonging to the [[Polynesian languages|Polynesian language]] family spoken by about 200 people on [[Penrhyn Island]] and other islands in Northern [[Cook Islands]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Penrhyn|url=http://www.ethnologue.com/language/pnh|publisher=Ethnologue|accessdate=7 March 2013}}</ref> It is considered to be an [[Endangered languages|endangered language]] as many of its users are shifting to [[Rarotongan language|Rarotongan]] and [[English language|English]].
